cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with optimization problems in online advertising, which involves game theory (cs.GT) in terms of the interaction between the service provider and client companies, information theory (cs.IT) in terms of modeling the stochastic properties of users' queries and click-through behaviors, networking (cs.NI) in terms of making connections to scheduling problems in wireless networks and stochastic networks, data structures (cs.DS) in terms of designing an online algorithm to capture the stochastic properties of the system, and machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of click-through rate estimation.
